description.plain:
Sonny Moore found club and mainstream stardom beginning in 2008, when he swapped his gig as post-hardcore frontman for From First to Last and created the dancefloor-oriented project, Skrillex. He initially used the name for live DJ sets, but in 2009 the project moved into the studio with Skrillex remixing the likes of Lady Gaga and Snoop Dogg.

Now he strives in mainstream success, playing monstrous live sets, releasing songs that rack up millions of listens and producing for the likes of Justin Bieber, A$AP Rocky, Ty Dolla Sign, and Ellie Goulding, and formed the duo Jack U with equally successful producer Thomas “Diplo” Pentz.

description.plain:
In “Make It Bun Dem,” Skrillex teams up with reggae artist Damian Marley to create a reggaestep banger. As with a lot of Skrillex’s music during the early-to-mid-2010s, the song never gained much popularity on the US Billboard Hot 100, but gained buzz as a part of internet culture, mainly after its inclusion during the mission “Kick the Hornet’s Nest” in the incredibly popular open-world action-adventure first-person shooter video game Far Cry 3 later that year.

The track was eventually re-released along with seven remixes on the Make It Bun Dem After Hours EP.

description.plain:
http://instagram.com/p/jvDOXJlhum/

The long awaited genre-masher from the biggest name in dubstep, Skrillex, and up-and-coming MC Chance The Rapper, “Coast Is Clear” is taken from Skrill’s debut album Recess (2014). Oddly, Skrillex had built a career on EPs up until this point, so the album release is something of a career milestone.
